Introduction

Song Yuni, known under her stage name Keena, is a South Korean rapper, singer-songwriter, and composer under ATTRAKT. She is best known as the main rapper, sub vocalist, oldest member and center of the girl group FIFTY FIFTY.

Keena debuted with the girl group FIFTY FIFTY, appearing first in their pre-release music video “Lovin’ Me” on November 14, 2022. The group officially made their debut with “The Fifty” released on November 18, 2022.

In a video from Genie Music Youtube channel, published on September 30, 2024, Keena revealed that she had legally changed her name from Song Jakyung to Song Yuni.
